  "body": "## Feature Issue\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n- [ ] If the request to join a community is ignored or unattended by the Admin/Community Manager for more than seven (7) days, the request should be marked as `expired`, and the community  \"Join request\" notification from Admin/Community Manager's Activity Center should be `deleted`.\r\n\r\n![1 line](https://user-images.githubusercontent.com/19339952/224416735-04cf3ec3-ed56-4e7f-a85e-aeec63e5aa35.png)\r\n\r\n- [ ] The Sender/Requester should be able to request again after seven (7) days\r\n- [ ] The Sender/Requester's Activity Center notification should be updated accordingly. (Tracked here: #15082)\r\n\r\n\r\n### Developer Notes\r\n\r\nThis feature requires an update on `status-go` for\r\n- marking the request as expired after seven (7) days if the request is ignored\r\n- removing the Join request notification on Admin/Community Manager's Activity Center\r\n- allowing the user (sender/requester) to request again after seven (7) days",
